# Kitchen Mode Interaction Rules

## Screen Layout (top to bottom)

1. Macro summary bar — live projected totals (saved + draft items)
2. Draft meal cards — scrollable, pop in as items are recognized
3. Listening indicator — waveform/pulse showing mic is active
4. Save + Cancel buttons

## Voice Flow

On-device STT listens continuously, auto-segments on pauses. Transcript segments are sent via WebSocket. Backend parses via Gemini, looks up food (custom → USDA → voice-guided creation), streams results back.

## Card States

- **Normal**: name, quantity, macros, source icon. Tappable for manual edit.
- **Clarifying**: card highlights/pulses, question text appears on card. TTS speaks question.
- **Creating**: fields fill in one-by-one as user speaks nutrition info during custom food creation.

## No-Match Flow

When no match in custom foods or USDA: TTS asks "Would you like to create it?" If yes, walk through serving size → calories → protein → carbs → fat via TTS. Card updates per field. User can tap card to finish manually. If no, item is dropped.

## Session Exit

- Save/Done: persist all draft entries + keep custom foods
- Navigate away: auto-save (same as done)
- Cancel: discard draft entries AND custom foods from this session. Show confirmation first.

## Defaults

- Missing quantity: default to 1 serving, add card, user corrects if needed
- Multiple USDA results: auto-pick most generic/common match silently
